title: $:/changenotes/5.4.0/#9836
description: Fix mid-text link cutoff and add configurable MaxLinks cap in Freelinks
tags: $:/tags/ChangeNote
release: 5.4.0
change-type: bugfix
change-category: plugin
github-links: https://github.com/TiddlyWiki/TiddlyWiki5/pull/9836
github-contributors: s793016

Fixes links silently stopping mid-text in long tiddlers, and adds a
configurable cap on rendered links per text node.

Fixes:
* Mid-text link cutoff caused by `search()` truncating results before the
  render stage; moved the cap to `$:/config/Freelinks/MaxLinks` (default 500)
  so text beyond the limit is preserved as plain text rather than lost.
* Incorrect failure links for long patterns caused by a hard depth limit in
  `buildFailureLinks()`; removed as the chain depth is naturally bounded.
* Unnecessary cache rebuilds triggered by draft edits and system tiddler
  changes such as tab clicks.

Improvements:
* `$:/config/Freelinks/MaxLinks` added to control rendered link count, with
  a settings panel input field for convenience.
